This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE JUDGE ON RETURN OF THE BENCH WARRANT.

Defendant Takeya M Calvin-Swope not in court.  Attorney Thomas Evangelos Harris in court for Takeya M Calvin-Swope.  Attorney Patrick J Anderson in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for a scheduling conference. Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a Bench Warrant to be issued REMAND TO JUDGE. No action taken on bail.

Defendant Takeya Marie Calvin-Swope in court in person.  Attorney Thomas Evangelos Harris appeared by video for Takeya Marie Calvin-Swope.  Prosecuting attorney Abby Rockendorf in court in person for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case set for a Preliminary Hearing. Parties are advised that this case is assigned to Branch 11, Judge Swanson. Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing. Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Court held colloquy with defendant. Probable cause has been found and the defendant is bound over for trial. Original Information e-filed, copy given to defense counsel who waived reading. Defense enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of the defendant. Case is adjourned to Br. 11.
Scheduling conference scheduled for September 19, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire & Waiver
Branch 25 tolls the time limits for the preliminary hearing.

Attorney Thomas Evangelos Harris in court.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court appointed attorney Harris as counsel on this case.  Same condition as defendant's other felony cases.  On motion of defense the 8/1/2022 preliminary hearing is adjourned.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 23, 2022 at 08:30 am.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT TO REPORT TO THE MILWAUKEE COUNTY JAIL (CJF) TO BE BOOKED AND RELEASED BY 5:00 P.M. ON 07-21-2022. IF THEY FAIL TO APPEAR, A BENCH WARRANT WILL BE ISSUED FOR THEIR ARREST.
Oral No Contact Order with McDonald's on 7170 North Teutonia Avenue.

Defendant Takeya Marie Calvin-Swope in court with attorney Michael V Fuentes.  Alexander James Geocaris appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Reserve Judge John Franke.  Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing in Branch PE.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 1, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 7/19/22 @ 1:30p
